## Step Reference Rules

- `example_refs` must cite real step IDs from the session data. Never fabricate.
- Each session's valid indices are listed on its `STEPS_AVAILABLE: [...]` line. Cite ONLY indices from that list.
- `start_step_id` / `end_step_id` accept either the digits after `step_id=` (e.g. `"7"` for `[step_id=7] USER:`) or the full opaque step identifier printed in the digest (e.g. `"msg_01SP..."`). Either form resolves against the session.
- If a session has no `STEPS_AVAILABLE` line or its list is empty, OMIT all example_refs for that session. Cite fewer sessions rather than wrong indices.
- NEVER reference sessions by ID, index, or UUID in text fields (description, rationale). Describe patterns in general terms.
